description.narrative: UNICEF supported the Government to implement the National Plan of Action to End Violence Against Women and Children (NPA-VAWC) Integrated Communication and Outreach Strategy. Kigoma and Mbeya Regions developed regional communication plans that will serve as a model for other regions. More than 9,000 parents and caregivers were reached with education on positive parenting to help reduce violence in homes, whilst also encouraging active involvement of men in child-rearing and promoting gender equality. Male and female teachers are better equipped to provide guidance and counselling services to students. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2020
